                            <comment id="70803" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2013 01:10:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b6717d88-4462-11e3-8472-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b6717d88-4462-11e3-8472-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sanity-lfsck test_9a failed also:&lt;br/&gt;
Error: &apos;(7) Expect &apos;completed&apos;, but got &apos;scanning-phase1&apos;&apos; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ldiskfs scrub speed in my local VM environment is not slower than 5&apos;000 objs/sec, even if ZFS scrub speed is only 1/10 of the ldiskfs, it should finished in time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="70800" author="adilger" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2013 23:59:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this only failing tests when the ZFS scrub code is enabled via &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7149&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7149&lt;/a&gt; so this isn&apos;t actually a failure on the current master branch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We still want to land that patch, but only once this problem is fixed. Is it possible that the ZFS scrub is just slower than ldiskfs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
